{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"465e2648-cf2f-46ab-b5cd-93f7e7050608","content":"Use `#if` preprocessor directives with MAUI's platform target constants to conditionally register each implementation:\n\n```csharp\n// MauiProgram.cs\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, iOSNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `ANDROID`, `IOS`, and `WINDOWS` are predefined by the MAUI SDK per target framework.\n- Each platform build only compiles its own branch, so missing platform assemblies won't cause errors.\n- Place each implementation in the corresponding `Platforms/<name>/` folder so it's only compiled for that target.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f90e86b4-2bd4-475b-bac8-a323215b3bc2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"045C:34A53A:B65354:CFF822:6A027B96"},"id":"c79839cf-263d-4ef0-b8a5-a1ba5603d625","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:00:14.065Z","parentId":"fceca28f-ec38-4c1e-9fc6-56ba8f74b41c"}
